title: Prep Wrestling: Douglas County wrestlers dominate Myrtle Point invitational
title_page: Prep Wrestling: Douglas County wrestlers dominate Myrtle Point invitational
maintext:
MYRTLE POINT — Douglas County wrestler swept the Myrtle Point Invitational, taking the top four spots in the competition.
Roseburg led the way with 221 points and wins by Kahleb Diaz at 126, Riley Rose at 145, Darian Thacker at 152 and Doran Gillespie at 182.
Glide finished second behind wins from Gage Dill (113), Zach Holland (160) and Collyn Potter (220).
Cole Waldron of Douglas won the 132-pound match with a pin of Glide’s Gabe Syverson in 1:10 to help his team to a third place finish.
Other county winners were South Umpqua’s Nakai Sinohui and Reedsport’s Devin Lichte.
Sinohui pinned Douglas’ Jacob Huse in 3:33 in the 138-pound match.
In the 170-pound match Lichte pinned Roseburg’s Owen Vredenburg in 51 seconds.
Reedsport finished fourth while South Umpqua had a tenth place finish and Riddle finished 11th with 16 points.
Team Scores
1. Roseburg, 221; 2. Glide, 192; 3. Douglas, 100; 4. Reedsport, 85.5; 5. Coquille, 73.5; 6. Myrtle Point, 57; 7. Klamath Union, 48; 7. Rogue River, 48; 9. Bonanza, 44; 10. South Umpqua, 38; 11. Riddle, 16.
